summary: Adds over 2000 rabbits to skyrims landscape, and or replace horrible creatures, like sabre cats and wolves, with friendly rabbits, making your travels safer.
descriptionHtml:
[center][color=#f1c232][size=3]／(^ x ^)＼[/size][/color][color=#ead1dc]Wabbit Season [/color][color=#cccccc][size=3]／(^ x ^=)＼[/size][/color][s][color=#cccccc]
[/color][/s]
There are two versions of this mod

[color=#ead1dc]More rabbits version:[/color] Adds over 2000 [color=#ead1dc]rabbits[/color] to tamriel, so they will be a much more common site, [color=#fff2cc]good[/color] for hunters but not good for [color=#b6d7a8]lettuce [/color]farmers

[color=#d5a6bd]Enemy Replacer version:[/color] Replaces [color=#cc0000]predator[/color] spwaners with [color=#ead1dc]rabbits[/color], so there will be a lot less [color=#ff0000]wolves [/color]and [color=#e06666]sabre cats[/color], and more [color=#ead1dc]rabbits[/color] instead.


You can install both versions and have both working simultaneously, but that will mean allot of [color=#ead1dc]rabbits[/color]


Thanks for trying the mod
[color=#7f6000]
[size=3]／(≡・ x ・≡)＼[/size]
[/color]

Note: i recommend not saving over game if you are just trying out the replacer version, as it actually changes the spawners to something else it will cause problems if uninstalled from a save that uses it[/center]
author: AlaintheGreat
